<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Imagine that you are a financial regulator, an=
d consider the general proposition:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">There is some crypto entity, some com=
pany that does something=C2=A0in the crypto industry.</li>=09<li style=3D"m=
argin-bottom: 5px;">Regular people give it their dollars or crypto for some=
 purpose.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It gives them back some =
sort of crypto receipt, saying =E2=80=9Cwe owe you one dollar=E2=80=9D or =
=E2=80=9Cwe owe you one crypto=E2=80=9D or whatever.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At a very high level of generality, what do yo=
u think about that? What I would say is:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">In 2013,=C2=A0you probably thought =E2=
=80=9Cah, yes, this entity is doing a fraud, and plans to steal the money o=
r crypto.=E2=80=9D But (1) you didn=E2=80=99t think about it that=C2=A0<em>=
much</em>, since these entities tended to be small and cater to a small nic=
he of crypto enthusiasts,=C2=A0and (2) it is not like the crypto entity was=
 coming to your office to have meetings with you.</li>=09<li style=3D"margi=
n-bottom: 5px;">In 2021, you probably thought =E2=80=9Cah, yes, innovation,=
 let us work with this crypto entity to build the future of finance on the =
blockchain.=E2=80=9D Unless you were the US Securities and Exchange Commiss=
ion; they never really thought that. But otherwise. The New York Department=
 of Financial Services was <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
